Author: claude-opus47-app <claude-opus47-app@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 23 12:41:59 2026 +0800

    feat(ldc): DEC-V61-050 batch 1 — v_centerline as independent observable
    
    Adds Ghia 1982 Table II v(x) on horizontal centerline y=0.5 as a
    genuinely independent physical observable to the LDC Compare tab,
    closing the honesty gap left by V61-049 (which promoted 5 "views"
    of the same u_centerline data).
    
    Batch 1 deliverables:
    - knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml: replace prior
      mislabelled v_centerline block (axis "y" but Table II x-indexed
      values) with Ghia's native 17-point non-uniform x grid + exact
      Table II v values. No interpolation — linear interp over Ghia's
      0.23→0.5 gap underestimates the curve. Cross-verified against
      scripts/flow-field-gen/generate_contours.py:103-110 which had
      encoded the same 17 points since V61-007. physics_contract
      precondition #4 flipped to satisfied_by_current_adapter=true;
      contract_status → SATISFIED_FOR_U_AND_V_CENTERLINE.
    - scripts/populate_ldc_v_centerline_post_hoc.py: NEW idempotent
      post-hoc VTK populator. Reads existing reports/phase5_fields
      /lid_driven_cavity/20260421T082340Z/VTK/*.vtk, interpolates U
      at 17 Ghia-native x points + 129 uniform render points onto
      y=0.05 line via pyvista. Writes both sample/1000/vCenterline.xy
      (legacy path the comparator reads) and postProcessing/sets/1024/
      vCenterline_U.xy + vCenterlineGold_U.xy (modern path the updated
      generator would write). No simpleFoam re-run — same underlying
      audit field, just a line the old generator didn't emit.
    - src/foam_agent_adapter.py::_emit_phase7a_function_objects: add
      vCenterline lineUniform set so future LDC runs produce v_centerline
      natively; post-hoc populator no longer needed for new fixtures.
    - ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py: _load_sample_xy gains
      value_col parameter (u uses col 1, v uses col 2 for U_y on a
      horizontal line). New _load_ldc_v_gold() helper. build_report_
      context now computes metrics_v_centerline + paper_v_centerline
      when the gold has a v_centerline block and the fixture has a
      vCenterline.xy.
    - ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx: Comparison
      ReportContext type expands with metrics_v_centerline? +
      paper_v_centerline?. MultiDimensionComparePanel gains D6 section
      rendering v verdict (12/17 at ±5%) + L²/L∞/max/RMS + per-point
      dev. Dimension counter increments. Honesty footer rewrite:
      v_centerline now GREEN (supported); only primary_vortex_location
      remains RED (batch 3 scope).
    
    Post-hoc sanity: 13/17 points within ±5% (L2=0.00406, max |dev|=
    5.73% interior; endpoints have divide-by-zero artifact from
    _compute_metrics gold=0 guard — separate small PR scope).
    
    Batches 2-4 scoped in DEC but not started:
    - Batch 2: ψ streamfunction extraction infrastructure
    - Batch 3: primary vortex (x_c, y_c) + ψ_min vs Ghia Table III
               (fixes gold YAML's wrong 0.7650 → 0.7344)
    - Batch 4: secondary vortices BL/BR vs Ghia Table III
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

