    feat(ldc): DEC-V61-050 batch 2 — streamfunction ψ extraction infrastructure
    
    New module ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py. Not wired into any
    caller yet — a deliberate scope boundary so this infra can land and
    be reviewed independently of the batch 3 (primary vortex) and batch 4
    (secondary eddies) comparator wiring.
    
    Method: compute ψ(x, y) on a uniform nx × ny grid by integrating
      ψ(x, y) = ∫₀^y U_x(x, y') dy'
    along columns (trapezoidal, numpy). Resamples the unstructured
    OpenFOAM VTK volume onto the uniform grid via pyvista .sample().
    
    Rationale for integration over ∇²ψ = −ω_z solve: needs only U_x + numpy
    trapz, whereas the Poisson approach needs scipy.sparse.linalg or a
    custom multigrid, and the accuracy difference on a 129² grid is
    dominated by the underlying mesh/sampling errors, not the ψ-equation
    discretization.
    
    Cache: {vtk_dir}/.psi_cache_{nx}x{ny}.npz keyed by VTK mtime — sampling
    a 20k-cell unstructured grid onto 129² ≈ 17k points is ~100ms, worth
    caching across repeated calls.
    
    API (both functions fail-soft, return None on pyvista/VTK missing):
      compute_streamfunction_from_vtk(vtk_path, nx=129, ny=129)
