      the D7 dimension — u_centerline/v_centerline are not gated on it.
    - Adds metrics_primary_vortex + paper_primary_vortex to the API
      context. Both null when extraction fails or gold missing.
    
    Backend (ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py):
    - Move pyvista import after cache check so a backend whose python
      interpreter lacks a working pyvista/vtk install can still serve
      ψ-derived dimensions if the cache was pre-populated out-of-band
      (e.g. via python3.11 running this module's __main__). This is
      real for this repo: system python3.9 has a broken vtkmodules
      install and the uvicorn server runs there; python3.11 has clean
      pyvista 0.47.1 and populates the cache.
    
    Frontend (ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx):
    - ComparisonReportContext expands with metrics_primary_vortex +
      paper_primary_vortex optional fields.
    - MultiDimensionComparePanel gains D7 section: 2D position + ψ_min
      with independent pass/fail ticks per-component. Verdict color
      (emerald when all_pass, amber when partial) drives border/badge.
    - Dimension counter increments to 7.
    - Honesty footer rewrite: only secondary vortices (BL/BR Ghia
      Table III cells 3-4) remain as NOT-YET-VALIDATED (batch 4 scope);
      v_centerline AND primary vortex now both GREEN with visible
      links to D6 and D7 respectively.
    
    Live API smoke-test on existing 20260421T082340Z fixture:
      x_meas = 0.6172 (gold 0.6172) — position_pass=True
      y_meas = 0.7344 (gold 0.7344) — position_pass=True
      ψ_meas = -0.10319 (gold -0.10342, 0.23% err) — psi_pass=True
      all_pass = True
      position_error = 2.8e-5 (well under tol 0.02)
    
    Simulation quality attested: simpleFoam on the harness's 129² mesh
    reproduces Ghia Table III primary vortex to grid quantization in
    position and within 0.23% in ψ strength. This is materially stronger
    validation evidence than the u_centerline profile alone.
    
    Cache artifact produced offline:
      reports/phase5_fields/lid_driven_cavity/20260421T082340Z/VTK/
        .psi_cache_129x129.npz (68 KB, gitignored with the rest of
        phase5_fields/*/20*/)
    The cache is regenerated on demand by running
      python3.11 ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py
    which is idempotent and runs in ~2s.
    
    Batch 4 scope unchanged: add BL (0.0313, 0.0391, +1.749e-6) and
    BR (0.9453, 0.0625, +1.254e-5) from Ghia Table III as new gold
    YAML block + comparator dimension D8.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

