knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:85:      evidence_ref: "DEC-V61-050 batch 4 (2026-04-23) added the secondary_vortices gold block with Ghia Table III Re=100 values (BL: 0.0313, 0.0391, ψ=+1.749e-6; BR: 0.9453, 0.0625, ψ=+1.254e-5) and wired a corner-windowed ψ-argmax extractor. Codex round 1 MED #2 (2026-04-23) flagged that the current ∫U_x dy' + pyvista resampling method has ψ wall-closure residual ≈ 3.4e-3 on the 20260421T082340Z fixture — 2000× LARGER than the BL ψ_gold (1.75e-6) and 270× larger than BR ψ_gold (1.25e-5). The coordinate matches found by argmax are therefore in a noise-dominated regime, not a validated physics reproduction. `metrics_secondary_vortices.eddies[*].all_pass` is now gated on signal_to_residual_ratio ≥ 3.0, so both eddies correctly report all_pass=False on the current pipeline. TRUE satisfaction of this precondition requires either (a) a Poisson solve ∇²ψ = -ω_z with ψ=0 walls, which eliminates integration-constant drift, or (b) OpenFOAM-native streamfunction sampling at the fixture mesh — both outside DEC-V61-050 scope (→ future DEC)."
knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:86:  contract_status: "SATISFIED_FOR_U_V_AND_PRIMARY_VORTEX_NOT_SECONDARIES — u_centerline (Table I), v_centerline (Table II), and primary_vortex_location (Table III primary row) are all Ghia-faithful and exercised by the audit comparator. secondary_vortices block is written and the extractor is wired, but Codex round 1 MED #2 confirmed BL/BR ψ magnitude is 2-3 decades below the ∫U_x trapezoidal integration's wall-closure residual, so those observables are currently reported as all_pass=False with a noise-floor caveat on the UI. DEC-V61-050 closure 2026-04-23: 3 of 4 Ghia Re=100 observables validated; secondaries require a Poisson-based ψ solve in a future DEC."
